{"parse":{"title":"John Christopher Bartholomew","pageid":15621560,"revid":821179525,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:John_G_Bartholomew_monument,_Dean_Cemetery.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/John_G_Bartholomew_monument%2C_Dean_Cemetery.jpg/220px-John_G_Bartholomew_monument%2C_Dean_Cemetery.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"330\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/John_G_Bartholomew_monument%2C_Dean_Cemetery.jpg/330px-John_G_Bartholomew_monument%2C_Dean_Cemetery.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/John_G_Bartholomew_monument%2C_Dean_Cemetery.jpg/440px-John_G_Bartholomew_monument%2C_Dean_Cemetery.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2056\" data-file-height=\"3088\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:John_G_Bartholomew_monument,_Dean_Cemetery.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Bartholomew monument, Dean Cemetery</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:John_Christopher%27s_name_at_the_foot_of_the_Bartholomew_monument.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/John_Christopher%27s_name_at_the_foot_of_the_Bartholomew_monument.JPG/220px-John_Christopher%27s_name_at_the_foot_of_the_Bartholomew_monument.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"146\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/John_Christopher%27s_name_at_the_foot_of_the_Bartholomew_monument.JPG/330px-John_Christopher%27s_name_at_the_foot_of_the_Bartholomew_monument.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/John_Christopher%27s_name_at_the_foot_of_the_Bartholomew_monument.JPG/440px-John_Christopher%27s_name_at_the_foot_of_the_Bartholomew_monument.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3088\" data-file-height=\"2056\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:John_Christopher%27s_name_at_the_foot_of_the_Bartholomew_monument.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>John Christopher's name at the foot of the Bartholomew monument</div></div></div>\n<p><b>John Christopher Bartholomew</b> (or <b>J.C. Bartholomew</b>) (15 January 1923 \u2013 16 January 2008) was a <a href=\"/wiki/Scotland\" title=\"Scotland\">Scottish</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Cartography\" title=\"Cartography\">cartographer</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Geography\" title=\"Geography\">geographer</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Life\">Life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Christopher_Bartholomew&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Bartholomew was the son of Marie Antoinette Sarolea, daughter of <a href=\"/wiki/Charles_Sarolea\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Charles Sarolea\">Charles Sarolea</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/John_(Ian)_Bartholomew\" title=\"John (Ian) Bartholomew\">John (Ian) Bartholomew</a> (1890\u20131962). <sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He was the great-great-grandson of the founder of <a href=\"/wiki/John_Bartholomew_and_Son_Ltd.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"John Bartholomew and Son Ltd.\">John Bartholomew and Son Ltd.</a>\n</p><p>He studied at <a href=\"/wiki/Edinburgh_Academy\" title=\"Edinburgh Academy\">Edinburgh Academy</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Gordonstoun\" title=\"Gordonstoun\">Gordonstoun</a> before taking a degree in geography at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Edinburgh\" title=\"University of Edinburgh\">University of Edinburgh</a>.\n</p><p>He took over directorship of <a href=\"/wiki/John_Bartholomew_%26_Co.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"John Bartholomew &amp; Co.\">John Bartholomew &amp; Co.</a> from his father in 1951. At this stage Peter Bartholomew (1924-1987) was Chairman and Robert Bartholomew (b.1927) was production manager. The company's most memorable production during their control was the <i>Times Atlas</i> (five volumes but also available in a 'concise' version). It also published the first metric versions of the large scale <a href=\"/wiki/Ordnance_Survey\" title=\"Ordnance Survey\">Ordnance Survey</a> maps of the UK, aimed at hikers and travellers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Bartholomew served as president of the <a href=\"/wiki/British_Cartographic_Society\" title=\"British Cartographic Society\">British Cartographic Society</a> in 1970\u201371. He was also a vice-president of the <a href=\"/wiki/International_Cartographic_Association\" title=\"International Cartographic Association\">International Cartographic Association</a>, 1972\u201380, and from 1987 to 1993, he was president of the <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Scottish_Geographical_Society\" title=\"Royal Scottish Geographical Society\">Royal Scottish Geographical Society</a>. He was  active on the committee of the Scottish Rights of Way Society (now ScotWays), and was made its honorary president.\n</p><p>On his death he left monies to pay for view indicators on the summits of both <a href=\"/wiki/Berwick_Law\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Berwick Law\">Berwick Law</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/Braid_Hills\" title=\"Braid Hills\">Braid Hills</a>.\n</p><p>He is buried against the north wall of the 20th century extension to <a href=\"/wiki/Dean_Cemetery\" title=\"Dean Cemetery\">Dean Cemetery</a> in western <a href=\"/wiki/Edinburgh\" title=\"Edinburgh\">Edinburgh</a> at the memorial to his grandfather, <a href=\"/wiki/John_George_Bartholomew\" title=\"John George Bartholomew\">John George Bartholomew</a>. His father Ian, and uncle Hugh lie with him.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Christopher_Bartholomew&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Family\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He married Ginette Achard-James. They had five sons: John Eric, Philip, Christopher, Patrick and Ivon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Christopher_Bartholomew&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" 